From: Marcin FM <marcin@lgic.pl>
Subject: [PATCH] Adapt spreadsheet dates to Fedora calamine
Upstream-context-author: Na'aman Hirschfeld <nhirschfeld@gmail.com>
Upstream-context: https://github.com/kreuzberg-dev/kreuzberg/commit/1b63779dd38cf042007739ccb3d1d2f3aacb697d

Use Fedora's calamine release and its DateTime conversion API. The upstream
commit above introduced the newer to_ymd_hms_milli() call carried by v4.10.2;
this Fedora-specific compatibility patch reverses only that API selection and
is not a backport of the upstream commit.

diff --git a/crates/kreuzberg/Cargo.toml b/crates/kreuzberg/Cargo.toml
--- a/crates/kreuzberg/Cargo.toml
+++ b/crates/kreuzberg/Cargo.toml
@@ -195 +195 @@ bytes = { workspace = true }
-calamine = { version = "0.36.0", features = ["dates"], optional = true }
+calamine = { version = "0.24.0", features = ["dates"], optional = true }
diff --git a/crates/kreuzberg/src/extraction/excel.rs b/crates/kreuzberg/src/extraction/excel.rs
--- a/crates/kreuzberg/src/extraction/excel.rs
+++ b/crates/kreuzberg/src/extraction/excel.rs
@@ -594,4 +594,4 @@ fn format_cell_to_string(data: &Data) -> String {
-        Data::DateTime(dt) => {
-            let (year, month, day, hour, min, sec, _milli) = dt.to_ymd_hms_milli();
-            format!("{:04}-{:02}-{:02} {:02}:{:02}:{:02}", year, month, day, hour, min, sec)
-        }
+        Data::DateTime(dt) => dt
+            .as_datetime()
+            .map(|value| value.format("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S").to_string())
+            .unwrap_or_else(|| dt.as_f64().to_string()),
